{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"ce2a03e4-331b-4658-9bff-0cde0e90708f","content":"PID 12345 isn't running on this machine, so I'll give you the commands to run on your target system.\n\n## 1. Determine the Runtime\n\nRun these on the host where the app is running:\n\n```bash\n# Method 1: Check for CoreCLR shared library in the process\ncat /proc/12345/maps | grep -i coreclr\n```\n\n- **If you see `libcoreclr.so`** → it's **CoreCLR**\n- **If nothing matches** → it's likely **NativeAOT**\n\n```bash\n# Method 2: Check if the binary is self-contained native\nfile /proc/12345/exe\n```\n\n- CoreCLR binaries show as a standard ELF that loads the CLR dynamically.\n- NativeAOT binaries are fully statically linked (no `libcoreclr.so`).\n\n---\n\n## 2. Configure Crash Dumps\n\n### If CoreCLR\n\nSet these **environment variables** before launching the app (e.g. in your systemd unit or wrapper script):\n\n```bash\nexport DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump=1          # Enable automatic dump on crash\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpType=4            # 4 = Full dump (1=Mini, 2=Heap, 3=Triage, 4=Full)\nexport DOTNET_DbgMiniDumpName=/var/dumps/coredump.%p.%t  # %p=PID, %t=timestamp\n```\n\nOptionally ensure the dump directory exists:\n\n```bash\nsudo mkdir -p /var/dumps && sudo chmod 1777 /var/dumps\n```\n\n### If NativeAOT\n\nNativeAOT apps don't have the managed `DbgMiniDump` infrastructure. Use the **Linux kernel core dump** mechanism instead:\n\n```bash\n# 1. Enable core dumps (no size limit)\nulimit -c unlimited\n\n# 2. Configure the kernel core pattern\necho '/var/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee /proc/sys/kernel/core_pattern\n\n# 3. Make it persistent across reboots\necho 'kernel.core_pattern=/var/dumps/core.%e.%p.%t' | sudo tee -a /etc/sysctl.d/99-coredump.conf\nsudo sysctl --system\n```\n\nIf your system uses **systemd-coredump** (check with `coredumpctl`), dumps are already collected under `/var/lib/systemd/coredump/` and you can retrieve them with:\n\n```bash\ncoredumpctl list        # list recent dumps\ncoredumpctl dump 12345  # extract a specific dump\n```\n\n---\n\n### Quick summary\n\n| | CoreCLR | NativeAOT |\n|---|---|---|\n| **Detection** | `libcoreclr.so` in `/proc/PID/maps` | No CLR libraries loaded |\n| **Dump mechanism** | `DOTNET_DbgEnableMiniDump` env vars | Linux kernel `core_pattern` / systemd-coredump |\n| **Analysis tool** | `dotnet-dump analyze` / `lldb` + SOS | `lldb` / `gdb` (native debugging) |\n\nRun the detection commands first and let me know which runtime it is — I can help further with analysis tooling or systemd service configuration.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bd2def1b-08d7-4bdf-bc83-be80765572ce","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The process doesn't exist on this machine, which makes sense — the user is asking for guidance, not necessarily running the process here. Let me provide diagnostic steps and configuration guidance.","outputTokens":867,"requestId":"D811:283A56:3567E98:3A74CC0:69FBF1B1"},"id":"503fbf1d-b437-4ada-824e-6124ec6c575e","timestamp":"2026-05-07T01:58:27.913Z","parentId":"4cb41161-a995-4661-b39c-6222e61000af"}
